definition.value: Quantification of the change in hemoglobin levels in an individual over time, eg over the course of several years after regular blood donation.
Quantification of the levels of N-acylethanolamine in a sample.
Quantification of the volume of or amount contained in the left upper chamber of the heart.

Quantification of a muscle fiber cross-sectional area by muscle biopsy. It is a microscopic measure of muscle fiber size and structure to assess skeletal muscle hypertrophy typically in the context of resistance training.
Quantification of the levels of clozapine in blood plasma. Clozapine is an antipsychotic drug used to treat schizophrenia.

Quantification of the levels of N-desmethylclozapine, also known as norclozapine, in blood plasma. N-desmethylclozapine is a major active metabolite of clozapine, an antipsychotic drug used to treat schizophrenia.

Quantification of the ratio of clozapine to-N-desmethylclozapine, also known as norclozapine, in blood plasma. Clozapine is an antipsychotic drug used to treat schizophrenia and N-desmethylclozapine is a a major active metabolite of clozapine.
Quantification of the levels of clozapine in blood serum. Clozapine is an antipsychotic drug used to treat schizophrenia.

Quantification of the ratio of clozapine to-N-desmethylclozapine, also known as norclozapine, in blood serum. Clozapine is an antipsychotic drug used to treat schizophrenia and N-desmethylclozapine is a a major active metabolite of clozapine.

Quantification of the levels of N-desmethylclozapine, also known as norclozapine, in blood serum. N-desmethylclozapine is a a major active metabolite of clozapine, an antipsychotic drug used to treat schizophrenia.
Quantification of the volume of the kidney.
Quantification of the volume of the pancreas.
Quantification of the volume of the lung.
Quantification of the volume of the spleen.
Quantification of the volume of the liver.
Quantification of the fat content of the pancreas.
Quantification of the levels of leucine rich alpha-2-glycoprotein 1 present in a sample.
Quantification of the amount of complement factor H-related proteins in a sample.
Quantification of the amount of complement factor H-related protein 1 in a sample.
Quantification of the amount of complement factor H-related protein 2 in a sample.
Quantification of the amount of complement factor H-related protein 3 in a sample.
Quantification of the amount of complement factor H-related protein 4A in a sample.

Any of the various types of human blood whose antigen characteristics determine compatibility in transfusion. While the ABO and Rhesus sytems are the most well known, there are in total about 300 different blood type antigens distributed across 34 different blood type systems.
The ABO system consists of A and B antigens and antibodies against these antigens.
ABO phenotype A, corresponding to the genotype AO or AA.
ABO phenotype B, corresponding to the genotype BO or BB.
ABO phenotype AB, corresponding to the genotype AB.
ABO phenotype O, corresponding to the genotype OO.
Quantification of some aspect of the consumption of dietary nutritional supplements.
Quantification of some aspect of the consumption of mastiha, a natural nutritional supplement known to possess antioxidant and anti-inflammatory properties.
Quantification of the expression of a gene in a cell, tissue or sample.

label.value: tumor necrosis factor alpha gene expression measurement

definition.value: Quantification of the expression of the TNFA gene, which encodes tumor necrosis factor-alpha.
Quantification of the expression of IL-6 gene, encoding interleukin-6.
Quantification of glutathione peroxidase in a sample.
The result of a measurement of circulating human polyomavirus 6-specific antibodies.
Quantification of one or more antibodies to the WU polyomavirus, typically in serum.
Quantification of one or more antibodies to the human polyomavirus 6, typically in serum.
Quantification of some aspect of stimulant use, for instance in the treatment of ADHD.
Quantification of the change in cardiac troponin I in an individual over time, typically measured in blood.
Quantification of glucocorticoid receptor gene expression.
Quantification of time an individual spends outside.
Quantification of some aspect of the use of insulin.
Number of times bowels opened per day.
An interval measured from the onset of the P wave in one PQRST wave complex to the onset of the P wave in the following PQRST wave complex.

A narrow or occludable angle is when the angle of the eye is narrow or closed by the iris. Occludable anterior chamber angle is considered as a primary risk factor for primary angle closure glaucoma (PACG).
Quantification of the ratio between absolute lymphocyte count and absolute monocyte count.

Quantification of the rate at which small molecules cross the peritoneal membrane typically measured as the ratio of the concentration of creatinine in the dialysate at 4 hours of a dwell of dialysate solution to that in the plasma (4-hr D/P creatinine).
Quantification of the amount of complement factor H-related protein 4 in a sample.
Quantification of complement factor H-like 1 protein in a sample.
Quantification of some aspect of skin roughness such as frequency or severity.
